jority of kids in private school are not wealthy.  The difference is that these people want their children to have a good education and be safe.  They are willing to pay to get that done rather than put up a futile fight against school administrations, teachers unions, and politicians all while their children get a subpar education and are quite literally in danger from gangs, violence and ramped drug abuse.  To Ms. Benedikt, if you want to improve public schools then run for office instead of blaming &quot;wealthy people&quot;. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="832" language="en" documentId="4146" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Biff Pucaruba" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:45PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="14" thumbsDown="0" origId="4146" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="832"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>